title: Irish Sirloin Steak and Twice-cooked Potatoes with broccoli in pesto, walnut and balsamic dressing
description: Both the earthiness of the basil and the sharpness of the cheese in the pesto are accentuated by the balsamic vinegar in the to-die-for drizzle that accompanies this dish. Potatoes are twice cooked for a crispy golden finish, while the Irish sirloin steak is made to be cooked exactly as you like it.
